1
00:00:00,160 --> 00:00:03,578
The Botpleng I know is you.

2
00:00:03,709 --> 00:00:05,272
It has always been you, dude.

3
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,850
You’re Tontharn, right?

4
00:00:07,750 --> 00:00:09,098
This might seem too early

5
00:00:09,490 --> 00:00:11,025
but I think I like you.

6
00:00:11,490 --> 00:00:13,185
Can we get to know each other?

7
00:00:15,060 --> 00:00:16,050
(In my life, )

8
00:00:16,080 --> 00:00:17,723
(I’ve never gotten to choose anything.)

9
00:00:17,750 --> 00:00:20,560
(Just going with what’s chosen for me.)

10
00:00:20,589 --> 00:00:22,770
(I’m an orphan my parents chose to abandon.)

11
00:00:23,260 --> 00:00:25,665
(The kind housemom chose to take me in.)

12
00:00:26,540 --> 00:00:27,694
(Growing up a little more, )

13
00:00:27,723 --> 00:00:29,963
(a kind family chose me to adopt.)

14
00:00:30,180 --> 00:00:33,170
(I was chosen to save his child’s life.)

15
00:00:40,940 --> 00:00:41,940
Hey!

16
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:45,643
Let go of me, Tan!

17
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:47,280
Let go of me, Tan!

18
00:00:47,316 --> 00:00:48,218
Let go of me, Tan!
Don’t do it, Thun.

19
00:00:49,156 --> 00:00:50,174
You can’t do it.

20
00:00:50,950 --> 00:00:52,792
If you get hurt, I’ll get hurt too.

21
00:00:53,540 --> 00:00:54,792
Let go, Tan!

22
00:00:55,170 --> 00:00:56,640
Tell me what’s wrong.

23
00:00:56,669 --> 00:00:57,883
I’ll help you.

24
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:00,400
What if I have a problem with Dad?

25
00:01:00,450 --> 00:01:01,520
How would you help me?

26
00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:11,410
You had a fight with Dad again?

27
00:01:14,390 --> 00:01:15,832
I don’t want to be like Dad.

28
00:01:17,650 --> 00:01:19,210
I don’t want to study what Dad studied.

29
00:01:20,014 --> 00:01:22,010
I don’t get why he has to force me.

30
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,000
I love the violin.

31
00:01:24,710 --> 00:01:26,043
I want to learn about the violin.

32
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:28,130
I don’t know when I’m going to die.

33
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,934
I just want to live life the way I want.

34
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:38,785
I’ll talk to Dad.

35
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:41,810
I’ll study that instead of you.

36
00:01:47,898 --> 00:01:49,440
But don’t you want to become a doctor?

37
00:01:50,450 --> 00:01:53,905
I want you to live life the way you want.

38
00:01:55,430 --> 00:01:56,430
As for me.

39
00:01:57,520 --> 00:01:58,778
I can be anything.

40
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:03,810
If you love the violin and want to play it,

41
00:02:04,770 --> 00:02:06,225
then do it all you want.

42
00:02:16,790 --> 00:02:17,790
Tan.

43
00:02:24,390 --> 00:02:25,390
(That’s right.)

44
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:26,887
(I can be anything.)

45
00:02:27,570 --> 00:02:28,800
(I’m used to it.)

46
00:02:29,498 --> 00:02:31,500
(To live the life others choose for me.)

47
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:37,447
(But he came in and changed it.)

48
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:44,690
(After meeting Tontharn, )

49
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,785
(it was the first time)

50
00:02:47,050 --> 00:02:49,476
(that I think about living a life for myself.)

51
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:04,900
Hello.

52
00:03:05,670 --> 00:03:06,865
My name is Tankhun.

53
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:09,701
You’re Tontharn, right?

54
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:14,770
It might seem too early

55
00:03:15,930 --> 00:03:17,280
but I think I like you.

56
00:03:19,418 --> 00:03:21,032
Can we get to know each other?

57
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:02,305
Here it is.

58
00:05:02,341 --> 00:05:04,218
Fresh vegetable salad with lots of tomatoes.

59
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,301
Just the way you like it.

60
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:10,967
Thank you.

61
00:05:13,190 --> 00:05:14,101
It’s alright.

62
00:05:14,130 --> 00:05:16,094
I was only adding the dressing to the vegetables.

63
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,974
Thanks for coming back to me.

64
00:05:23,110 --> 00:05:24,378
So that means

65
00:05:25,130 --> 00:05:26,610
you’re letting me make my moves?

66
00:05:29,990 --> 00:05:31,047
You know

67
00:05:32,625 --> 00:05:33,898
how I feel, right?

68
00:05:36,980 --> 00:05:38,000
You’re confused.

69
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,200
Happy.

70
00:05:40,490 --> 00:05:41,490
And afraid.

71
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,541
When a person feels this way,

72
00:05:46,790 --> 00:05:48,567
how can he love anyone, Tan?

73
00:05:49,687 --> 00:05:51,690
The Tontharn inside me is empty.

74
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:54,298
Full of guilt for Pleng.

75
00:05:55,190 --> 00:05:55,723
I’m afraid that who I really am

76
00:05:55,745 --> 00:05:57,898
wouldn’t be the one you love.

77
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,807
I’m afraid that I might hurt you.

78
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,189
I’m not ready to love, Tan.

79
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,440
The only thing I fear in life

80
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:16,465
is not having you in my life.

81
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,960
No matter how you want to live your life,

82
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:23,498
you can go at it all you want.

83
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:26,654
Just let me stay beside you.

84
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:31,592
Whenever you’re ready to love,

85
00:06:32,836 --> 00:06:35,025
I’ll be waiting for that day, Tontharn.

86
00:06:45,570 --> 00:06:47,970
Actually, I didn’t like vegetables
because of how they taste.

87
00:06:49,330 --> 00:06:49,854
But when I was younger,

88
00:06:49,876 --> 00:06:51,578
vegetables were easier to find than meat.

89
00:06:55,940 --> 00:06:57,141
This is Tontharn.

90
00:06:58,690 --> 00:07:00,690
A poor child with no preferences.

91
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:02,669
No dreams.

92
00:07:04,310 --> 00:07:05,978
Let’s get to know him together, Tan.

93
00:07:10,490 --> 00:07:12,930
Nice to meet you, Tontharn.

94
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:18,989
(The life I want for myself)

95
00:07:19,585 --> 00:07:21,590
(is living with this person.)

96
00:07:22,570 --> 00:07:25,498
(Doesn’t matter if he’s Botpleng or Tontharn.)

97
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:30,974
Soft or fluffy?

98
00:07:31,850 --> 00:07:32,850
Soft.

99
00:07:37,992 --> 00:07:39,949
Cooling or dense.

100
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:42,430
Cooling.

101
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:51,578
White or black?

102
00:07:52,390 --> 00:07:55,185
Are you pulling my legs?

103
00:08:02,140 --> 00:08:03,527
I want to get to know you quickly.

104
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,243
So we can become close in no time.

105
00:08:06,650 --> 00:08:08,000
You’re giving me headaches.

106
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:11,723
Headaches?

107
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:13,410
You look so happy, though.

108
00:08:13,850 --> 00:08:15,570
I’ve never seen you smile like this before.

109
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:17,818
How can you?

110
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:19,550
We’ve just got to know each other.

111
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:22,020
Hey!

112
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,818
How can you do that to someone you just met?

113
00:08:26,790 --> 00:08:27,425
I’m not okay with this.

114
00:08:27,461 --> 00:08:28,461
Get out.

115
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:29,660
Go away.

116
00:08:31,410 --> 00:08:33,185
You’re the one who waltzed into my house.

117
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:36,261
I’m only arresting the intruder.

118
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,200
Tan!

119
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:40,792
Hey!

120
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,472
This is not it!

121
00:08:57,710 --> 00:08:58,603
See?

122
00:08:58,640 --> 00:09:00,458
I told you it would look good here.

123
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:02,450
Yeah.

124
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,178
It’s your turn now.

125
00:09:06,310 --> 00:09:08,007
Hmm? What?

126
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,040
Well.

127
00:09:12,940 --> 00:09:15,469
I want to know the one who’s hitting on me, too.

128
00:09:16,509 --> 00:09:18,510
Tell me about your childhood.

129
00:09:18,890 --> 00:09:19,890
Sure.

130
00:09:20,090 --> 00:09:21,090
What do you want to ask?

131
00:09:25,716 --> 00:09:27,934
Why did you want to become a criminologist?

132
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:32,698
Actually, I didn’t want to become a criminologist.

133
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:34,800
I studied it instead of Thunphob.

134
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,930
I actually wanted to become a doctor.

135
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:41,570
Not quite, actually.

136
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,069
I wanted to be anything

137
00:09:43,380 --> 00:09:45,723
that can make my adoptive parents proud.

138
00:09:47,352 --> 00:09:49,350
But I’ve just found a new life,

139
00:09:49,690 --> 00:09:50,967
after meeting you.

140
00:09:52,970 --> 00:09:53,985
A new life?

141
00:09:58,850 --> 00:10:00,407
A life where I want to be with you.

142
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:06,980
Hey.

143
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:08,676
We’ve just got to know each other.

144
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,883
How can you do this?

145
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:11,760
Oh?

146
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:14,378
Didn’t you want to get to know me?

147
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:17,992
I just want to try a one-night stand.

148
00:10:30,810 --> 00:10:32,632
This is not me giving consent to this.

149
00:10:33,590 --> 00:10:36,218
Because for me, there’s only

150
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:40,094
every night forever.

151
00:11:25,930 --> 00:11:26,930
Thank you.

152
00:11:32,780 --> 00:11:34,116
Dao confessed.

153
00:11:35,541 --> 00:11:37,621
She didn’t want me to be the one
who solved the case.

154
00:11:38,330 --> 00:11:39,956
She’s the type to not give in to anyone

155
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:42,000
even when it comes to things like this.

156
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:46,320
At least her craziness brought the case to a close.

157
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,378
Now it’s time for my businesses

158
00:11:51,300 --> 00:11:52,516
that have to be ended.

159
00:11:59,460 --> 00:12:00,923
Why are you resigning?

160
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:03,139
If you’re stressed, then you can take a break.

161
00:12:03,163 --> 00:12:05,160
You can take as many day-offs you want.

162
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,250
How many?

163
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:08,720
3 months?

164
00:12:09,850 --> 00:12:10,894
Fine, 6 months?

165
00:12:12,340 --> 00:12:13,340
Right.

166
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:15,069
Thanks a lot.

167
00:12:15,970 --> 00:12:17,658
I’m only becoming a journalist

168
00:12:18,010 --> 00:12:19,745
because it’s Pleng’s dream.

169
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:21,710
I think

170
00:12:22,790 --> 00:12:24,363
this is no longer a place for me.

171
00:12:24,974 --> 00:12:26,214
What are you going to do, then?

172
00:12:28,910 --> 00:12:30,494
I’m going to look for that answer.

173
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:33,512
I haven’t got to be myself for so many years.

174
00:12:33,534 --> 00:12:35,510
I don’t even know what I like to do.

175
00:12:49,665 --> 00:12:50,665
Go for it.

176
00:12:51,050 --> 00:12:52,050
I’m rooting for you.

177
00:12:53,130 --> 00:12:54,545
But whoever you are,

178
00:12:55,110 --> 00:12:56,276
you’re still my friend.

179
00:13:00,790 --> 00:13:02,400
You’re so cliché.

180
00:13:04,370 --> 00:13:06,000
Are you really going to quit?

181
00:13:06,400 --> 00:13:07,090
Yeah.

182
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:10,523
Then who’s going to stop Boss when he’s angry?

183
00:13:10,567 --> 00:13:12,429
Don’t you feel sorry for us?

184
00:13:13,750 --> 00:13:15,672
He doesn’t want to be a journalist anymore.

185
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:18,370
Why are you pressuring my friend?

186
00:13:18,392 --> 00:13:19,716
Or do you…

187
00:13:20,990 --> 00:13:22,792
want to quit along with him?

188
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,901
Come on, Boss!

189
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:26,538
Mile!

190
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:29,700
Just kidding.

191
00:13:30,980 --> 00:13:31,980
Let’s go.

192
00:13:32,180 --> 00:13:33,810
Let’s have a farewell meal for Tontharn.

193
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:36,603
Can we do that later?

194
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:37,640
Huh?

195
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:39,070
I have an urgent appointment today.

196
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,640
Come on!

197
00:13:41,210 --> 00:13:42,676
What a miss!

198
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:44,167
Let’s do that next time.

199
00:13:57,430 --> 00:13:58,430
Kan.

200
00:13:58,790 --> 00:14:01,250
I have the maid prepare your food.

201
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:02,574
It will get cold.

202
00:14:05,190 --> 00:14:06,538
You can go ahead, Mom.

203
00:14:07,190 --> 00:14:08,385
I’m not hungry.

204
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:10,830
Hello.

205
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:24,770
Can we talk?

206
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,236
Sure, son.

207
00:14:28,538 --> 00:14:30,109
Have you eaten?

208
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:32,043
Let’s eat together.

209
00:14:33,018 --> 00:14:34,018
It’s alright.

210
00:14:36,150 --> 00:14:37,534
I’m just here to say goodbye.

211
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:57,360
Thank you so much, Mom Kan.

212
00:14:58,950 --> 00:15:00,400
For raising me like your own son.

213
00:15:03,610 --> 00:15:05,250
But I’m not Botpleng.

214
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,007
I’m not your child.

215
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:10,938
No, Tontharn.

216
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:14,014
You’re my son.

217
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:22,298
I made your family go through horrible things.

218
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:25,745
I don’t deserve to be your son.

219
00:15:28,790 --> 00:15:34,065
Goodbye, Mom Kan and Grandma.

220
00:16:31,110 --> 00:16:33,854
Thanks for not getting at me
for hypnotizing you.

221
00:16:34,550 --> 00:16:36,880
Also, sorry for everything so far.

222
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:45,840
It’s me who should apologize to you.

223
00:16:46,610 --> 00:16:47,610
It was because of me.

224
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:49,600
Because of my family,

225
00:16:51,149 --> 00:16:53,150
that you and Mom had to lose Pleng.

226
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:56,989
I should be thanking you.

227
00:16:58,410 --> 00:17:00,000
It’s because of your presence

228
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:03,090
that I still have Tontharn left.

229
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:06,232
Thank you so much.

230
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:11,287
Goodbye.

231
00:17:32,730 --> 00:17:33,730
Grandma.

232
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:36,203
From now on,

233
00:17:37,690 --> 00:17:39,592
you can miss Pleng all you want.

234
00:17:55,316 --> 00:17:57,905
6 MONTHS LATER.

235
00:17:57,934 --> 00:18:00,276
Keep taking good care of yourself like this, Tontharn.

236
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:02,458
You’re doing much better.

237
00:18:02,494 --> 00:18:04,763
If you have anything before the appointment date,

238
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:05,952
feel free to call me anytime.

239
00:18:06,230 --> 00:18:07,230
Thank you.

240
00:18:13,540 --> 00:18:16,589
Then, I’ll take your patient home.

241
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,327
Well, well.

242
00:18:18,378 --> 00:18:19,825
You’re always giving him a lift.

243
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:21,650
Never leave each other’s side like lovers.

244
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,680
Um, we’re not lovers yet.

245
00:18:26,247 --> 00:18:27,861
We’re just getting to know each other.

246
00:18:28,070 --> 00:18:29,672
We haven’t put a label on it yet.

247
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:34,058
Sounds so much like a Gen Z relationship.

248
00:18:34,087 --> 00:18:35,374
Are you okay with that, Tan?

249
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,240
Of course.

250
00:18:37,540 --> 00:18:39,357
As long as he’s in the talking stage with me only.

251
00:18:39,381 --> 00:18:40,240
I’m all good.

252
00:18:40,349 --> 00:18:41,418
Come on.

253
00:18:41,476 --> 00:18:42,523
I’m always with you.

254
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:44,400
How can I find time to talk to others?

255
00:18:45,470 --> 00:18:46,603
Are you saying that

256
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:48,185
because you’re thinking about doing it?

257
00:18:49,110 --> 00:18:50,618
Are you going to let me be by myself?

258
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:54,174
Not putting any label on it

259
00:18:54,458 --> 00:18:56,145
but so clear on the actions.

260
00:18:57,170 --> 00:18:58,472
Gen Z, indeed.

261
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:02,821
Then I’ll be leaving.

262
00:19:05,380 --> 00:19:06,380
See you.

263
00:19:26,090 --> 00:19:27,578
Have you started to realize your sin?

264
00:19:29,220 --> 00:19:30,530
I didn’t do anything wrong.

265
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:34,967
It’s you who’ve been fooled.

266
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,498
No matter how much you think you’re a victim,

267
00:19:38,790 --> 00:19:41,956
it’s not enough of a reason to kill someone.

268
00:20:00,810 --> 00:20:01,978
Becoming a murderer

269
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:04,923
was your choice.

270
00:20:06,790 --> 00:20:08,378
Therefore, it’s you who’s evil.

271
00:20:16,110 --> 00:20:17,287
Stop blaming others.

272
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,610
Stop finding reasons to justify yourself.

273
00:20:22,300 --> 00:20:23,592
You can’t fool anyone anymore.

274
00:20:24,260 --> 00:20:25,345
Except for yourself.

275
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:33,880
Where are you going?

276
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:37,949
I’m not guilty.

277
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:40,567
I’m not guilty!

278
00:20:40,970 --> 00:20:42,421
You guys are the evil ones.

279
00:20:42,443 --> 00:20:43,941
I’m not guilty!

280
00:20:43,978 --> 00:20:45,120
You devils!

281
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:46,792
You guys are the evil ones!

282
00:20:47,112 --> 00:20:48,298
I’m not guilty!

283
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:49,367
Where are you going?!
I’m not guilty!

284
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,240
Let go!

285
00:20:51,570 --> 00:20:52,570
Let go!

286
00:20:53,220 --> 00:20:55,156
I’m not guilty, let go of me!

287
00:20:55,192 --> 00:20:56,363
Let go!

288
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,400
Let go!

289
00:20:58,520 --> 00:20:59,956
I’m not guilty!

290
00:21:09,018 --> 00:21:10,218
Do you want me to go with you?

291
00:21:11,140 --> 00:21:12,140
It’s alright.

292
00:21:24,780 --> 00:21:26,603
I’m sorry, Tontharn.

293
00:21:37,680 --> 00:21:39,170
Are you settling in here alright?

294
00:21:47,510 --> 00:21:48,510
Sure.

295
00:21:49,207 --> 00:21:50,414
Easy.

296
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:55,178
At least I don’t have to run away

297
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,214
from the guilt,

298
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:01,461
or from the truth

299
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:04,763
that I can never escape.

300
00:22:08,040 --> 00:22:09,578
Please take care of yourself.

301
00:22:12,269 --> 00:22:13,269
Dad.

302
00:22:38,470 --> 00:22:39,790
Does your heart feel lighter now?

303
00:22:42,050 --> 00:22:43,050
Yes.

304
00:22:43,410 --> 00:22:46,050
But not quite entirely.

305
00:22:47,880 --> 00:22:48,901
Hey! Watch out!

306
00:22:49,930 --> 00:22:51,076
Sorry!

307
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:04,770
It’s been 6 months since that day.

308
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:11,040
Hey.

309
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:12,840
I thought you said you could wait.

310
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:14,480
I can wait.

311
00:23:14,990 --> 00:23:16,349
Just want to know

312
00:23:16,350 --> 00:23:17,550
if you’ve leaned in to me yet.

313
00:23:23,580 --> 00:23:25,185
In Tontharn’s heart,

314
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:27,963
how far have I come through?

315
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:38,960
Just know that

316
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,440
in here,

317
00:23:42,890 --> 00:23:44,174
there’s only you.

318
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:45,520
Okay?

319
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:47,630
Yeah.

320
00:23:48,350 --> 00:23:49,870
Even if I have to wait my entire life,

321
00:23:50,140 --> 00:23:51,140
I’m up for it.

322
00:23:55,090 --> 00:23:56,090
Hey.

323
00:23:57,550 --> 00:23:59,149
Come on. Let’s go.

324
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:08,167
TITLE DEED.

325
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:11,352
This is where you can hear the waterfall, Tontharn.

326
00:24:15,590 --> 00:24:16,990
You want me to call you a rich man?

327
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,116
I’m inviting you to invest.

328
00:24:24,430 --> 00:24:25,430
This is the place.

329
00:24:26,250 --> 00:24:29,018
Thunphob wanted to give Botpleng.

330
00:24:31,110 --> 00:24:34,778
This is where you can hear the water source.

331
00:24:36,970 --> 00:24:37,970
And this place

332
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:44,414
is where you’ll get to achieve your dream.

333
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:50,887
How did you know

334
00:24:50,930 --> 00:24:52,480
that I want to run a homestay?

335
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:59,898
I want to build a home

336
00:25:01,090 --> 00:25:02,923
for those searching for a home like me.

337
00:25:07,210 --> 00:25:08,836
But isn’t this too much?

338
00:25:09,510 --> 00:25:11,738
I don’t have any money to invest with you.

339
00:25:13,610 --> 00:25:14,610
I know.

340
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:22,276
So I brought you this.

341
00:25:30,370 --> 00:25:32,130
LOAN AGREEMENT.

342
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:34,327
The interest rate with the bank is expensive.

343
00:25:34,363 --> 00:25:35,803
You’ll need a long time to pay back.

344
00:25:35,850 --> 00:25:38,574
You’ll have to take longer to achieve things.

345
00:25:40,450 --> 00:25:41,746
Are you not going to wait for me?

346
00:25:41,770 --> 00:25:43,061
When I say I’m going to wait,

347
00:25:43,410 --> 00:25:44,640
I mean it.

348
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,792
But can’t I have a little shortcut?

349
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:49,527
Instead of paying the high interest rate to the bank,

350
00:25:49,950 --> 00:25:51,578
I’d rather you give that money to me.

351
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:53,323
I won’t make the interest too high.

352
00:25:53,700 --> 00:25:54,860
Won’t be harsh on you either.

353
00:25:56,310 --> 00:25:57,630
I’m sick of this rich man’s face.

354
00:26:12,990 --> 00:26:14,720
Are you going to look for another rich man?

355
00:26:15,265 --> 00:26:17,270
I’m going to make money
to pay back the rich man.

356
00:26:19,070 --> 00:26:21,250
Thank you for waiting.

357
00:26:22,690 --> 00:26:24,000
I want you to know

358
00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:25,832
that you’re not alone.

359
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:29,010
Whenever you want to fuel up,

360
00:26:30,190 --> 00:26:31,476
you can come and hug me.

361
00:26:34,250 --> 00:26:35,345
Who would want that?

362
00:26:39,243 --> 00:26:40,243
Hmm.

363
00:26:41,980 --> 00:26:43,876
RAI YAI YAEM HOMESTAY.

364
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:46,040
I’m giving you only this once.

365
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,545
Plus a ‘one night’?

366
00:26:49,850 --> 00:26:51,105
You’re driving me crazy!

367
00:26:54,130 --> 00:26:55,130
Thank you.

368
00:28:09,500 --> 00:28:11,054
It’s like a dream come true.

369
00:28:13,847 --> 00:28:15,025
Congratulations.

370
00:28:17,970 --> 00:28:19,469
What about you?

371
00:28:20,140 --> 00:28:21,192
Do you have a dream?

372
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:25,970
Well.

373
00:28:27,150 --> 00:28:28,240
A dream?

374
00:28:30,530 --> 00:28:32,029
I might not have had it in the past,

375
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:34,152
but I do now.

376
00:28:36,430 --> 00:28:38,050
I want to build a peaceful world

377
00:28:38,072 --> 00:28:39,200
for the people I love.

378
00:28:40,350 --> 00:28:43,723
So I’m happy working with the police.

379
00:28:45,780 --> 00:28:47,418
To get to know what the criminals think

380
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,585
so we can fix it

381
00:28:50,170 --> 00:28:51,330
and prevent things in time.

382
00:28:54,760 --> 00:28:56,101
Just like how you helped me.

383
00:29:02,150 --> 00:29:03,454
If I haven’t met you,

384
00:29:05,210 --> 00:29:07,338
I would have been living life as I was told.

385
00:29:09,340 --> 00:29:10,770
You’re the inspiration

386
00:29:11,130 --> 00:29:13,178
for me to have a dream, Tontharn.

387
00:29:16,260 --> 00:29:17,374
Without you,

388
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:20,712
I wouldn’t have dared to dream either.

389
00:29:41,985 --> 00:29:45,694
FIRST LOVE HOMESTAY.

390
00:29:49,396 --> 00:29:50,396
One second.

391
00:29:56,710 --> 00:29:57,710
Hello?

392
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:02,087
Yes, First Love Homestay.

393
00:30:03,850 --> 00:30:05,367
You can send it in the morning.

394
00:30:05,980 --> 00:30:07,767
Yes, thank you so much.

395
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:21,520
Don’t say it.

396
00:30:21,850 --> 00:30:23,760
We have to wake up early tomorrow.

397
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:26,040
Let’s go to bed.

398
00:30:29,670 --> 00:30:30,676
Tontharn.

399
00:30:31,840 --> 00:30:32,989
I’m a man.

400
00:30:33,032 --> 00:30:34,632
I’m also a man!

401
00:30:34,669 --> 00:30:36,698
But tomorrow is our homestay’s opening day.

402
00:30:38,980 --> 00:30:40,232
We need to save our energy.

403
00:30:40,910 --> 00:30:41,910
Come!

404
00:30:44,030 --> 00:30:45,030
Hurry up, Tan.

405
00:30:47,990 --> 00:30:48,990
Tan!

406
00:30:51,701 --> 00:30:53,381
FIRST LOVE HOMESTAY.

407
00:30:53,410 --> 00:30:55,076
Congrats, Tontharn.

408
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:56,443
Thank you, Doc Jen.

409
00:30:57,300 --> 00:30:58,300
You too.

410
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:01,607
I’m happy you realize what you want to do

411
00:31:01,658 --> 00:31:03,272
and you’re doing it so well.

412
00:31:03,860 --> 00:31:05,294
I’m so proud of you, dude.

413
00:31:06,414 --> 00:31:07,592
I wouldn’thave made it,

414
00:31:11,610 --> 00:31:12,610
without him.

415
00:31:14,790 --> 00:31:16,065
So…

416
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:18,683
How long are you going to keep
my brother on the hook?

417
00:31:20,070 --> 00:31:21,070
Right.

418
00:31:21,350 --> 00:31:23,032
Waiting is torture.

419
00:31:25,061 --> 00:31:27,030
It’s not him who’s being tortured.

420
00:31:33,590 --> 00:31:34,870
What are you guys talking about?

421
00:31:36,870 --> 00:31:38,320
About a sadist

422
00:31:38,349 --> 00:31:39,934
who likes to torture himself.

423
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:52,785
Um, is that Madam Kedsara?

424
00:31:59,910 --> 00:32:00,910
Grandma.

425
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:04,327
I brought you some home fragrances.

426
00:32:04,363 --> 00:32:06,109
The guests will love the nice smell

427
00:32:06,283 --> 00:32:07,469
and they’ll keep coming back.

428
00:32:09,830 --> 00:32:11,403
Thank you so much, Grandma.

429
00:32:17,010 --> 00:32:19,767
What about Mom Kan?

430
00:32:21,500 --> 00:32:22,618
Ask her yourself.

431
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,498
Pleng used to say that.

432
00:32:44,430 --> 00:32:46,283
I’ve always wanted you to be my mother.

433
00:32:47,265 --> 00:32:48,574
I never thought.

434
00:32:50,870 --> 00:32:53,192
I would get to become your son as Pleng.

435
00:32:55,030 --> 00:32:56,821
It was a short time

436
00:32:58,250 --> 00:33:01,418
that showed me the warmth of a mother
for the first time.

437
00:33:06,945 --> 00:33:11,190
But as Tontharn, who killed Pleng,

438
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:15,330
I don’t know if you still want me as a son.

439
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:24,189
Tontharn, my son.

440
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:32,712
I’ve done what Botpleng asked me to.

441
00:33:36,120 --> 00:33:37,978
You’re my son, Tontharn.

442
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,669
Though right now,

443
00:34:06,710 --> 00:34:08,480
there have been so many new laws,

444
00:34:08,950 --> 00:34:12,312
we still can’t solve the criminal cases

445
00:34:12,334 --> 00:34:13,854
that are occurring in the present day.

446
00:34:19,050 --> 00:34:20,152
Would it be better

447
00:34:20,174 --> 00:34:22,363
to reduce the issue of crime

448
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:24,360
by preventing the occurrence?

449
00:34:27,260 --> 00:34:28,690
Um, aren’t there organizations

450
00:34:28,720 --> 00:34:30,690
that are dealing with this?

451
00:34:30,727 --> 00:34:34,669
Like the ONCB or the Royal Thai Police?

452
00:34:34,712 --> 00:34:35,294
Yes.

453
00:34:35,640 --> 00:34:37,983
But they’re more focused on
fixing the problem after it’s occurred,

454
00:34:38,007 --> 00:34:39,752
rather than preventing them.

455
00:34:40,700 --> 00:34:43,963
My dream is to build a unit

456
00:34:44,014 --> 00:34:46,494
that focuses on preventive measures

457
00:34:46,516 --> 00:34:47,716
rather than capturing.

458
00:34:47,767 --> 00:34:50,610
Analyzing data to forecast criminal action

459
00:34:50,640 --> 00:34:52,014
in risky areas.

460
00:34:52,500 --> 00:34:55,461
In the UK, there’s
the Neighborhood Policing Team

461
00:34:55,490 --> 00:34:57,847
which focuses on community relationships

462
00:34:57,883 --> 00:34:59,018
to reduce the crime rate.

463
00:35:00,230 --> 00:35:01,054
Professor.

464
00:35:01,098 --> 00:35:04,625
Will our country ever achieve that?

465
00:35:05,710 --> 00:35:07,156
I will make it happen.

466
00:35:09,070 --> 00:35:10,480
Starting with small steps

467
00:35:10,516 --> 00:35:12,189
by teaching you guys

468
00:35:12,225 --> 00:35:14,190
to read a criminal’s body language.

469
00:35:24,269 --> 00:35:25,269
You know what?

470
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:28,283
The name “First Love Homestay”

471
00:35:29,020 --> 00:35:32,567
came from Botpleng and Thunphob.

472
00:35:33,949 --> 00:35:35,301
It’s not that hard to figure out.

473
00:35:36,630 --> 00:35:37,630
What about you?

474
00:35:38,683 --> 00:35:40,923
You used to say that
looking at this place makes you sad.

475
00:35:42,410 --> 00:35:43,730
Has that changed?

476
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:46,880
I now fall in love when I look at it.

477
00:35:49,690 --> 00:35:51,585
Thun and Botpleng would be glad.

478
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:54,690
That their first love can change this place.

479
00:35:59,540 --> 00:36:01,163
What about you?

480
00:36:01,930 --> 00:36:03,178
Aren’t you happy

481
00:36:04,540 --> 00:36:05,978
that when I look, I feel

482
00:36:07,950 --> 00:36:08,950
love.

483
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:23,105
Did you just

484
00:36:24,670 --> 00:36:25,774
say you love me?

485
00:36:27,800 --> 00:36:29,090
Love a dog, maybe!

486
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:30,894
I love the one I was looking at.

487
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:35,818
Thank you.

488
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:37,240
For waiting.

489
00:36:38,390 --> 00:36:40,785
Thank you for telling me to follow my heart.

490
00:36:41,990 --> 00:36:42,990
Otherwise,

491
00:36:44,421 --> 00:36:46,420
I wouldn’t have been this happy.

492
00:36:50,420 --> 00:36:51,650
I love you, Tan.

493
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:58,080
Tontharn.

494
00:38:06,380 --> 00:38:07,380
Tontharn.

495
00:38:12,250 --> 00:38:13,250
Tontharn.

496
00:38:15,830 --> 00:38:16,830
Tontharn.

497
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:24,880
Tontharn.

498
00:38:45,900 --> 00:38:47,156
(Try closing your eyes)

499
00:38:48,010 --> 00:38:49,847
(and see what you can hear.)

500
00:38:54,865 --> 00:38:57,483
How should I listen to the leaves
for them to resemble a melody?

501
00:38:58,334 --> 00:39:00,330
Even the sound of that waterfall is louder.

502
00:39:00,910 --> 00:39:01,910
A waterfall?

503
00:39:11,990 --> 00:39:13,070
The sound of the waterfall?

504
00:39:17,900 --> 00:39:18,900
Tontharn!

505
00:39:22,330 --> 00:39:23,985
Where are you, Tontharn?

506
00:40:16,650 --> 00:40:17,978
You once told me

507
00:40:19,338 --> 00:40:20,712
your name is “Tankhun”

508
00:40:22,210 --> 00:40:23,890
because you have to return others’ favors.

509
00:40:24,690 --> 00:40:26,530
But it’s not so.

510
00:40:35,450 --> 00:40:36,683
Your heart

511
00:40:38,490 --> 00:40:40,407
is so big and warm

512
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,778
that no one can ever replace you.

513
00:40:45,149 --> 00:40:47,150
Every time I call your name,

514
00:40:47,910 --> 00:40:49,192
I only think that.

515
00:40:50,167 --> 00:40:52,170
I have to love you even more.

516
00:40:53,410 --> 00:40:54,603
To return your favor

517
00:40:57,578 --> 00:40:58,578
of loving me.

518
00:41:00,380 --> 00:41:01,665
I really thank you

519
00:41:02,780 --> 00:41:03,780
for loving me.

520
00:41:05,590 --> 00:41:06,590
Thank you

521
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:08,440
for being here for me to love you.

522
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:20,574
Daisy, Daisy.

523
00:41:23,740 --> 00:41:27,374
Give me your answer, do.

524
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:37,454
Yes, I do.

525
00:42:39,770 --> 00:42:40,770
Mom said that

526
00:42:41,150 --> 00:42:42,750
you have to ask for permission yourself.

527
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:48,734
Pleng! Thun!

528
00:42:49,910 --> 00:42:51,207
Are you guys here?

529
00:42:52,070 --> 00:42:53,430
This is how you’re going to do it?

530
00:42:59,170 --> 00:43:01,192
Thun! Botpleng!

531
00:43:03,490 --> 00:43:05,265
I’m getting married to Tontharn!

532
00:43:10,740 --> 00:43:11,740
What’s next?

533
00:43:16,770 --> 00:43:18,770
I don’t know if you guys would mind.

534
00:43:19,890 --> 00:43:21,450
Even if you do, we’d still get married.

535
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:25,040
Tan!

536
00:43:25,750 --> 00:43:26,750
It’s true.

537
00:43:26,910 --> 00:43:28,785
I’m just asking out of courtesy.

538
00:43:30,090 --> 00:43:32,705
Pleng wouldn’t try to stop love.

539
00:43:33,240 --> 00:43:34,800
He loved seeing people love each other.

540
00:43:36,270 --> 00:43:37,105
Just like…

541
00:43:37,149 --> 00:43:38,952
How he wanted Mom Kan love me.

542
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:42,574
Thun was also that kind of person.

543
00:43:43,590 --> 00:43:44,910
He wanted Dad and Mom to love me.

544
00:43:50,970 --> 00:43:52,261
You guys are so nice.

545
00:43:56,260 --> 00:43:57,260
By now,

546
00:43:58,050 --> 00:44:01,141
they’d probably be riding a bike somewhere.

547
00:44:03,270 --> 00:44:04,494
Just like the two of us.

548
00:45:25,590 --> 00:45:27,110
Are you thinking of something naughty?

549
00:45:29,530 --> 00:45:30,530
No.

550
00:45:31,810 --> 00:45:32,952
I’m just thinking that

551
00:45:33,420 --> 00:45:34,523
it feels like a dream.

552
00:45:35,780 --> 00:45:37,309
That this handsome guy

553
00:45:37,750 --> 00:45:39,105
is becoming mine.

554
00:45:43,850 --> 00:45:45,454
Tontharn is a lovely kid

555
00:45:45,790 --> 00:45:47,985
but he always thinks otherwise.

556
00:45:48,021 --> 00:45:51,578
I used to think I should not love this boy.

557
00:45:52,790 --> 00:45:55,061
But time proved that

558
00:45:55,098 --> 00:45:57,060
you deserve to be loved.

559
00:45:58,300 --> 00:45:59,360
Thank you so much

560
00:45:59,880 --> 00:46:02,160
for making Khitakan happy

561
00:46:02,670 --> 00:46:04,901
and for making Botpleng happy, too.

562
00:46:06,410 --> 00:46:08,821
I hope your love life is filled with happiness.

563
00:46:09,400 --> 00:46:11,054
My youngest grandson.

564
00:46:26,160 --> 00:46:27,716
I have wronged you on so many things

565
00:46:28,680 --> 00:46:30,341
but you said that

566
00:46:30,378 --> 00:46:34,487
my love made your life better.

567
00:46:36,043 --> 00:46:38,040
I’ve always wanted to tell you

568
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:40,574
that you love

569
00:46:41,100 --> 00:46:42,930
have saved my life too.

570
00:46:44,930 --> 00:46:48,232
Without Tontharn becoming my son that day,

571
00:46:50,110 --> 00:46:52,574
I wouldn’t be here.

572
00:46:54,530 --> 00:46:57,200
Thank you for forgiving me

573
00:46:57,847 --> 00:46:59,850
and becoming my son again.

574
00:47:03,370 --> 00:47:04,574
From now on,

575
00:47:05,070 --> 00:47:07,694
please take care of my heart, Tankhun.

576
00:47:09,980 --> 00:47:11,149
My pleasure.

577
00:47:19,150 --> 00:47:21,150
Ever since I knew you, Tan,

578
00:47:21,614 --> 00:47:23,970
you’ve never asked for anything from the family.

579
00:47:24,390 --> 00:47:26,625
You only did what was asked of you.

580
00:47:26,950 --> 00:47:31,287
Today, I’ll be making just one more wish
on their behalf.

581
00:47:32,190 --> 00:47:35,701
I wish Tan and Tontharn,

582
00:47:36,090 --> 00:47:38,356
a love filled with never-ending happiness.

583
00:47:45,410 --> 00:47:47,163
What about the grooms?

584
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:49,160
Do you have anything to say to one another?

585
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:56,378
I still remember the first time I saw him.

586
00:47:59,180 --> 00:48:03,323
His eyes looked confused, like a lost man.

587
00:48:04,860 --> 00:48:06,189
But he was brave enough

588
00:48:07,270 --> 00:48:09,112
to find out the truth.

589
00:48:17,680 --> 00:48:21,403
He’s also kind, attentive,

590
00:48:21,950 --> 00:48:23,301
and cares for me

591
00:48:24,660 --> 00:48:26,378
even though he never said it out.

592
00:48:40,960 --> 00:48:42,538
He loves justice.

593
00:48:44,970 --> 00:48:46,290
He accepts the truth.

594
00:48:47,221 --> 00:48:50,130
He can forgive people, truly from his heart.

595
00:48:51,461 --> 00:48:53,505
I can never forgive myself.

596
00:48:55,610 --> 00:48:57,352
I don’t even deserve to be here.

597
00:49:00,220 --> 00:49:01,585
I’ve wronged Thunphob.

598
00:49:03,880 --> 00:49:05,418
I’ve wronged you, too.

599
00:49:07,720 --> 00:49:09,032
I am Tontharn.

600
00:49:10,870 --> 00:49:12,254
I’m not Botpleng.

601
00:49:14,990 --> 00:49:17,636
The one you love is Botpleng.

602
00:49:18,240 --> 00:49:19,490
He’s Tontharn,

603
00:49:21,040 --> 00:49:22,603
who made my heart

604
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:26,392
feel like it really comes alive

605
00:49:27,030 --> 00:49:28,030
for the first time.

606
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:37,149
I have already told him

607
00:49:37,860 --> 00:49:39,592
that no one can ever replace him.

608
00:49:42,680 --> 00:49:44,378
Every time I’m lost

609
00:49:45,550 --> 00:49:46,952
or faces darkness,

610
00:49:49,338 --> 00:49:51,340
there’s always him as my guiding light

611
00:49:53,450 --> 00:49:54,785
to give me warmth.

612
00:49:57,250 --> 00:49:59,970
I feel like I’m always embraced by love.

613
00:50:02,850 --> 00:50:04,778
He’s like the love in a melody

614
00:50:05,930 --> 00:50:07,672
that goes on endlessly to me.

615
00:50:34,870 --> 00:50:35,992
Argh!

616
00:50:40,669 --> 00:50:42,670
They say a wedding is exhausting,

617
00:50:43,430 --> 00:50:44,916
that’s so true, right, Tan?

618
00:50:46,501 --> 00:50:48,500
So you’re out of energy

619
00:50:48,530 --> 00:50:49,810
to make this handsome guy yours?

620
00:50:52,014 --> 00:50:53,014
Woah!

621
00:50:55,970 --> 00:50:57,156
My energy is back.

622
00:51:00,330 --> 00:51:01,636
Just kidding.

623
00:51:01,680 --> 00:51:03,032
You’ve had a long day.

624
00:51:03,054 --> 00:51:04,054
Get some rest.

625
00:51:09,070 --> 00:51:10,070
Hey!

626
00:51:12,110 --> 00:51:13,425
But I was being serious.

627
00:51:23,540 --> 00:51:25,301
Become ‘my’ handsome guy.
